div.p: Trap gate with DPL=3 for user-mode system calls
Bit 7: Present = 1 Bit 6-5: DPL = 11 (ring 3) Bit 4: System = 0 (gate) Bit 3-0: Type = 1111 (trap)
mov eax, SYSCALL_NUM mov ebx, arg1 mov ecx, arg2 mov edx, arg3 int 0x80 ; IDT[0x80] ; EAX = return value
DPL=3 allows user-mode (ring 3) code to execute INT 0x80 without GPF. Trap gate preserves IF so interrupts remain enabled during syscall handling.
